        "content": "<p>In a slight irony, the command that <a href=\"http://_genonce.sh\" title=\"http://_genonce.sh\">_genonce.sh</a> uses to detect if there is an internet connection actually fails if there isn't an internet connection. :). As a test for something else, I tried running the publisher using the gen script and got the following:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>jeanduteau@PowerBuck fhir-med-list % ./_genonce.sh\nChecking internet connection...\ncurl: (6) Could not resolve host: tx.fhir.org\n</pre></div>",
        "id": 194491103,
        "sender_full_name": "Jean Duteau",
        "timestamp": 1587152867
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the problem of course is that it is specifying a url which needs resolving - which needs an internet connection.  we should probably change that to the actual ip address for <a href=\"http://tx.fhir.org\" title=\"http://tx.fhir.org\">tx.fhir.org</a></p>",
